 <!-- Introduction -->
 <purpose>
 This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the assignment of visual attributes to shape models, geometric elements and annotation elements.  
<p>It specifies the resources for the assignment of visual attributes to styled models and geometric or annotation elements, but does not include specifications of those attributes.  
</p>
<p>   
This edition incorporates modifications of the previous edition. 
</p><p>
The following ARM EXPRESS declarations have been modified:</p>
<ul><li>
Styled_model;
</li></ul>
<p>The following ARM EXPRESS declarations have been added:</p>
<ul><li>
appearance_select;
</li></ul>
<p>The following ARM EXPRESS data types have been removed:</p>
<ul><li>
Appearance (replaced by appearance_select);
</li></ul>
<p>The definitions of the following ARM EXPRESS data types have been modified:</p>
<ul><li>
Styled_model;
</li></ul>

<p>In addition, modifications have been made to the mapping specification, the MIM schema and the EXPRESS-G diagrams to reflect and be consistent with the modifications of the ARM.</p>

 </purpose>

 <!-- Items in scope -->
 <inscope>
 	<li>identification of a model that contains annotation elements;</li>
   <li>association of visual attributes with styled models and elements.</li>
 </inscope>

 <!-- Items out of scope -->
 <outscope>
   <li>definition of views in which shape models, geometric elements or annotation are presented;</li>
   <li>specification of shape models;</li>
   <li>specification of annotations;</li>
   <li>specification of visual attributes;</li>
    </outscope>

